From: "Dave Shutler" <dave.shutler@acadiau.ca>

A Further Comment on the Bat Population of British Columbia
-----------------------------------------------------------
Although I appreciate that saying British Columbia has a "bat problem" may
be shorthand for "healthy bat population, some of which may transmit
diseases such as rabies" the former implies that something should be done to
eradicate bats, which should clearly not be considered a suitable response.
--
Dave Shutler
Department of Biology
Acadia University
Wolfville, NS
Canada B4P 2R6
<dave.shutler@acadiau.ca
